  "info": {
    "name": "Sales Funnel API",
    "description": "API documentation for Sales Funnel (Sales Visits) endpoints. This collection includes endpoints for managing sales visits, tracking progress through the sales funnel, generating various reports, and exporting data.\n\n## Base URL\n```\n/api/v1/sales/sales-visits\n```\n\n## Authentication\nAll endpoints require Bearer Token authentication.\n\n**Header:**\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <your_token>\n```\n\n## Progress Stages\n\n| Code | Stage       | Description                  |\n| ---- | ----------- | ---------------------------- |\n| `0`  | Plan        | Initial planning stage       |\n| `1`  | Visit       | Visit completed              |\n| `2`  | Opportunity | Opportunity identified       |\n| `3`  | Trial       | Product trial/test           |\n| `4`  | Quotation   | Quotation sent               |\n| `5`  | Negotiation | Price negotiation            |\n| `6`  | PO          | Purchase Order (Deal closed) |\n| `C`  | Cancel      | Cancelled                    |\n| `P`  | Pending     | Pending                      |\n\n## Visit Status\n\n| Code | Status | Description     |\n| ---- | ------ | --------------- |\n| `P`  | Plan   | Planned visit   |\n| `F`  | Finish | Visit completed |\n| `C`  | Cancel | Visit cancelled |\n\n## Status Codes\n\n| Code | Description                             |\n| ---- | --------------------------------------- |\n| 200  | OK - Request successful                 |\n| 201  | Created - Resource created successfully |\n| 400  | Bad Request - Invalid request data      |\n| 401  | Unauthorized - Missing or invalid token |\n| 404  | Not Found - Resource not found          |\n| 500  | Internal Server Error - Server error    |\n\n## Error Responses\n\n### Validation Error (400)\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Key: 'SalesVisitCreateRequest.Details' Error:Field validation for 'Details' failed on the 'required' tag\"\n}\n```\n\n### Not Found Error (404)\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"record not found\"\n}\n```\n\n### Unauthorized Error (401)\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"missing token\"\n}\n```\n\nor\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"invalid token\"\n}\n```\n\n### Internal Server Error (500)\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"failed to create visit: <error details>\"\n}\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n1. **Auto-generated Code**: Sales visit code is automatically generated in format `VIS-YYYYMMDD-XXXX` (e.g., `VIS-20240115-0001`)\n\n2. **Progress Transition**: Progress can only move forward. Moving backward more than 1 level is not allowed. Cancel and Pending can be set from any state.\n\n3. **Soft Delete**: Deleting a sales visit performs a soft delete (sets `deleted_at` timestamp), so the record is not permanently removed from the database.\n\n4. **Before Progress**: The `before_progress` field is automatically set when progress is updated, allowing you to track progress changes.\n\n5. **Total Value**: The `total_value` in visit details is calculated as `quantity * price`.\n\n6. **Pagination**: Default page size is 10. Maximum page size should be configured in the server.\n\n7. **Date Format**: All dates should be in `YYYY-MM-DD` format.\n\n8. **Authentication**: All endpoints require a valid Bearer token in the Authorization header.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
